How to install latest node.js in ubuntu

---> sudo apt-get install curl
---> curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_10.x | sudo -E bash -
---> sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

npm installed at

/usr/lib/node_modules/npm

we can add modules in the npm for our use

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

FOR YOUR UNDERSTANDING

1) Create a folder and go in the folder
2) type ---> npm init
3) package.json is installed
4) then install nodemailer ---> node install nodemailer
5) node_modules folder is created which has nodemailer folder
6) package.json recieves an entry about the newly installed package
7) if the node_modules is deleted but the package.json has an entry then simple type ---> node install
8) it will install the specific modules mentioned in the package.json file.
9) you can also check the folders and code in the nodemailer folder.
 
